author: Staff Reports sports@fosters.com
title: High School Roundup: St. Thomas girls blank Kennett
text: Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 3:15 AM By Staff Reportssports@fosters.com Posted Oct. 20, 2015 at 3:15 AM NORTH CONWAY — Jessie Blaisdell scored the game's only goal in the 18th minute as the St. Thomas Aquinas girls soccer team edged Kennett, 1-0, Monday in Division II. Maddie Dillow made four saves. Midfielder Hannah MacVane played well as did stopper back Morgan Bevins. The Saints (3-9-2) host Coe-Brown on Wednesday. Londonderry 2, Dover 1 LONDONDERRY — The Dover girls soccer team dropped a 2-1 decision Monday to Londonderry in Division I. Megan Morrison scored for the Green Wave (4-8-3) with an assist going to Karly Keenan. Audrey Muscato made 11 saves. Ali Lipinski and Abby Cooke played well in the back. BOYS SOCCER MANCHESTER — The Coe-Brown boys soccer team defeated Manchester West, 2-0, Monday in Division II action. Colin Cain and Zac Cote scored for the Bears. Corbin LeBlanc made four saves. The Bears (10-3-1) host Trinity on Tuesday. Raymond 2, Farmington 1 FARMINGTON — The Farmington boys soccer team dropped a 2-1 decision Monday to Raymond in Division III. Jake Richardson scored for the Tigers from Spencer Deland. Evan Dore made seven saves. Zach Gilman anchored the defense and Josh Walsh played well in the midfield. Farmington (5-10) visits Gilford on Thursday. Raymond is 6-5-3. VOLLEYBALL Dover 3, Nashua South 0 DOVER — The Dover girls volleyball team swept Nashua South, 3-0, Monday in Division I by scores of 25-17, 25-15, 25-13. Mary Zlotosch had 13 kills and three blocks, Lisa Bean had nine kills and Kate Murphy served 100 percent. The Green Wave (12-4) host Salem on Wednesday for senior night. South is 3-13. Spaulding 3, Bishop Guertin 2 ROCHESTER — The Spaulding volleyball team had to go five sets to beat Bishop Guertin, 3-2, Monday in Division I. The Red Raiders prevailed by scores of 25-21, 19-25, 25-20, 22-25, 15-13. Alie Vaillancourt and Brooke Creteau had 10 kills apiece and Hannah Douglas added nine. Casey Ford had 34 digs and Olivia Noonan dished out 42 assists. Spaulding (15-1) hosts Concord on Wednesday for senior night. BG is 11-5. By Staff Reports
